  "tips": [
    {
      "title": "No article for professions",
      "body": "Unlike English, German drops the article when stating professions: 'Ich bin Lehrer' (I am a teacher), not 'Ich bin ein Lehrer'. The article is only added with an adjective: 'Ich bin ein guter Lehrer'."
    },
    {
      "title": "Feminine job forms with '-in'",
      "body": "Almost all masculine professions have a feminine form ending in '-in': der Lehrer / die Lehrerin, der Arzt / die Aerztin. The plural feminine adds '-nen': die Lehrerinnen."
    },
    {
      "title": "'von Beruf' for asking about jobs",
      "body": "The standard way to ask someone's profession is 'Was sind Sie von Beruf?' (What is your profession?). Answer with: 'Ich bin ... von Beruf'."
    }
  ]
